üîπ Types of Iteration in C

1Ô∏è‚É£ for Loop
Used when the number of repetitions is known in advance. It combines initialization, condition checking, and update in one statement.

2Ô∏è‚É£ while Loop
Used when the number of repetitions is not known and depends on a condition that is checked before the loop body executes.

3Ô∏è‚É£ do-while Loop
Used when the loop body must execute at least once, because the condition is checked after executing the statements.
